1️⃣ What is the difference between Read Replica and Multi-AZ?
🔹 Read Replica
	• Used for performance (read scaling)
	• Creates a read-only copy of the primary database
	• Data is asynchronously replicated
	• Can be in same or different AZ
	• Used for read-heavy workloads
	• Manual failover (cannot auto-promote unless you do it)
🔹 Multi-AZ
	• Used for high availability & disaster recovery
	• Creates a standby replica
	• Data is synchronously replicated
	• Standby cannot be read
	• Automatic failover
	• Used for production reliability
📊 Comparison Table
Feature	Read Replica	Multi-AZ
Purpose	Performance	Availability
Read allowed	Yes	No
Replication	Async	Sync
Failover	Manual	Automatic
📌 Interview line:
	Read Replica is for performance, Multi-AZ is for high availability.

2️⃣ What are the types of Placement Groups?
Placement Groups control how EC2 instances are placed on hardware.
🔹 1. Cluster Placement Group
	• Instances placed close together
	• Low latency, high throughput
	• Used for HPC, big data
🔹 2. Spread Placement Group
	• Instances placed on separate hardware
	• High availability
	• Used for critical applications
🔹 3. Partition Placement Group
	• Instances divided into logical partitions
	• Each partition isolated
	• Used for large distributed systems (HDFS, Kafka)

3️⃣ You need to allow HTTP & HTTPS to public EC2 but block all other access. How?
✅ Solution: Security Group
🔹 Steps:
	• Open port 80 (HTTP) → 0.0.0.0/0
	• Open port 443 (HTTPS) → 0.0.0.0/0
	• Do NOT add any other inbound rules
	• Security Groups are deny by default
🔹 Why SG?
	• Stateful
	• Automatically blocks all other traffic
NACL too.
📌 Interview Tip:
	Use Security Groups, not NACLs, for instance-level access control.
	
	

4️⃣ How would you implement Lifecycle Policies to reduce S3 cost?
🔹 What are Lifecycle Policies?
Rules that automatically move or delete objects based on age.
🔹 Example Strategy:
	• Day 0–30 → S3 Standard
	• Day 30–90 → S3 IA
	• Day 90+ → Glacier
	• After 365 days → Delete
🔹 Benefits:
	• Lower storage cost
	• No manual effort
	• Automated
📌 Interview line:
	Lifecycle policies move objects to cheaper storage classes automatically.

