	22️⃣ I have lost my PEM file. How to connect to the EC2 instance?
	🔴 Important Point
		• You CANNOT directly connect to an EC2 instance if the PEM file is lost.
		• AWS does not store PEM files for security reasons.
	
	✅ Recovery Methods
	🔹 Method 1: Use EC2 Instance Connect
	✔ Only works if:
		• Amazon Linux
		• Port 22 open
		• Instance running
	📌 AWS Console → EC2 → Connect → EC2 Instance Connect
	
	🔹 Method 2: Detach Root EBS Volume (Most Common Interview Answer)
	Steps:
		1. Stop the instance
		2. Detach root EBS volume
		3. Attach volume to another EC2
		4. Mount the volume
		5. Edit ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
		6. Add new public key
		7. Reattach volume
		8. Start instance & login
	
	🔹 Method 3: Use SSM Session Manager
	✔ Requires:
		• SSM agent
		• IAM role
		• Internet/VPC endpoint
	
	📌 Interview Line:
		Lost PEM cannot be recovered, but access can be restored using EBS detach or SSM.
	
	23️⃣ Difference between Layer 4 and Layer 7 Load Balancer
	🔹 Layer 4 Load Balancer
		• Works at Transport Layer
		• Uses IP & Port
		• Very fast
		• No content inspection
	Example:
		• Network Load Balancer (NLB)
	
	🔹 Layer 7 Load Balancer
		• Works at Application Layer
		• Uses URL, headers, cookies
		• Supports routing rules
	Example:
		• Application Load Balancer (ALB)
	
	📊 Comparison
	Feature	L4	L7
	OSI Layer	4	7
	Routing	IP/Port	Path/Host
	Speed	Faster	Slightly slower
	Example	NLB	ALB
	
	24️⃣ What is NAT Gateway?
	✅ Definition:
	A NAT Gateway allows private EC2 instances to access the internet for outbound traffic without allowing inbound traffic.
	🔹 Key Points:
		• Used in private subnets
		• Only outbound access
		• Fully managed service
		• Highly available
	📌 Example:
	Private EC2 → NAT Gateway → Internet
	
	25️⃣ Difference between Internet Gateway and NAT Gateway
	Feature	Internet Gateway	NAT Gateway
	Purpose	Public internet access	Private outbound access
	Inbound	Yes	No
	Subnet type	Public	Private
	Direction	Two-way	One-way
	Attachment	VPC	Subnet
	📌 Interview Line:
		Internet Gateway is for public access, NAT Gateway is for private outbound access.
	
	26️⃣ Can we access a resource in one VPC from another VPC?
	✅ Answer:
	YES, using:
		• VPC Peering
		• Transit Gateway
		• VPN
		• Direct Connect
	📌 Most common method: VPC Peering
	
	27️⃣ What is VPC Peering Connection?
	✅ Definition:
	VPC Peering is a network connection that allows two VPCs to communicate privately using AWS internal network.
	🔹 Key Points:
		• No internet required
		• Low latency
		• CIDR blocks must not overlap
		• One-to-one connection
	📌 Use case:
	App in VPC-A → DB in VPC-B
	
	28️⃣ What is NACL (Network Access Control List)?
	✅ Definition:
	A NACL is a stateless firewall that controls traffic at the subnet level.
	🔹 Features:
		• Stateless (inbound & outbound rules needed)
		• Allows & Denies rules
		• Evaluated in order
		• Applies to all instances in subnet
	
	29️⃣ Difference between Security Group and NACL
	📊 Comparison Table
	Feature	Security Group	NACL
	Level	Instance	Subnet
	Type	Stateful	Stateless
	Rules	Allow only	Allow & Deny
	Rule order	Not ordered	Ordered
	Use case	Fine-grained	Network-wide
	📌 Interview Line:
		Security Groups are instance-level and stateful, NACLs are subnet-level and stateless.
	
